#Get the data from my State
cases <- data$ND[-length(data$ND)]
#split the data of training(data in 2020) and actual data of data I want to test (Jan.1.2021 to Feb.10.2021)
cases_2020 <- cases[1:345]
cases_2021 <- cases[346:(346+40)]
yy <- yy <- ts(cases_2020, frequency = 366, start = c(2020,22))     # coverts sales data as time series object with start date and frequency (daily and leap year here)
plot.ts(yy)                                             # ALWAYS plot time series to see patterns: trend, cycle, variance over time

adf.test(yy)                            # if p-value is large (> 0.10), then nonstationary
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  yy
## Dickey-Fuller = -3.1303, Lag order = 7, p-value = 0.09995
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
yd <- diff(yy, differences = 1)         
plot.ts(yd)                             # looks stationary visually

adf.test(yd)
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  yd
## Dickey-Fuller = -1.1336, Lag order = 6, p-value = 0.9162
## alternative hypothesis: stationary
yd2 <- diff(yy, differences = 2)            
plot.ts(yd2)                                # looks stationary visually

adf.test(yd2)
## Warning in adf.test(yd2): p-value smaller than printed p-value
## 
##  Augmented Dickey-Fuller Test
## 
## data:  yd2
## Dickey-Fuller = -12.355, Lag order = 6, p-value = 0.01
## alternative hypothesis: stationary

Step 2. Decide AR(p) or MA(q) or both ARMA(p,q). Use the stationary series from Step 1.

#p and q should be 0,1,2

# To decide AR(p), plot Pacf. For AR(p) => Pacf becomes zero at some lag p

Pacf(yd2, lag.max = 10)                 # Pacf suggests p = 3

# To decide MA, plot Acf. For MA(q) => Acf becomes zero at some lag q

Acf(yd2, lag.max = 10)              # Acf suggests q = 3

##SO p = 3, q =3, d =2 for ND data

calculate the weighted average based on AICC

forecasts <- list(m2.predict$mean, m3.predict$mean
              , m5.predict$mean, m7.predict$mean)
aiccs <- c(m2$aicc, m3$aicc,  m5$aicc, m7$aicc)
aic_weights <- exp((min(aiccs) - aiccs)/2)
aic_weights <- aic_weights / sum(aic_weights)
averaged_forecast_aicc <- Reduce(`+`, Map(`*`, forecasts, aic_weights))

mape_aicc <- mean(abs((cases_2021 - averaged_forecast_aicc) / cases_2021))*100
mape_aicc
## [1] 2.012067

#calculate the weighted average based on BIC

bics <- c(m2$bic, m3$bic,  m5$bic, m7$bic)
bic_weights <- exp((min(bics) -bics)/2)
bic_weights <- bic_weights / sum(bic_weights)
averaged_forecast_bic <- Reduce(`+`, Map(`*`, forecasts, bic_weights))

mape_bic <- mean(abs((cases_2021 - averaged_forecast_bic) / cases_2021))*100
